<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-06-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="671" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.4112/173: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Secretary to the President</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sanders</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rapid
                                        City, S. Dak.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-22"><hi rend="italic">June 22,
                                1927</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 3:40 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to your telegram 1 p.m. June 21st, the President suggests that
                            you talk informally with Great Britain and Japan without commitment.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Everett Sanders</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>